channel.title: I can't access my router
channel.description:
When i put in 192.168.1.1 into the address bar, it won't load my router page?
I just shut off my router and turned it back on and when I did that my ip changes, thus making me port forward again
but... i can't connect to my router?

item.title: I can't access my router
item.dc:creator: @kiwon kiwon
item.description:
@kiwon wrote:

Read what I said, i have already put in my gateway address

I can’t access my router

I’m using firefox and it says, “Problem Loading Page”

I have done this many times before, but now it won’t work

item.title: I can't access my router
item.dc:creator: @Ash_o_lee Ash o lee
item.description:
@Ash_o_lee wrote:

First go to run in your start menu.
Type “cmd” in your run.
Then a command prompt opens. Type ipconfig/all then a whole
bunch of stuff you should come up on your command prompt.
Look for gateway. Then thats what you put in address bar.

Read full topic
